        "**Weak white noise** requires only zero covariance. It is possible for $\\varepsilon_t$ and $\\varepsilon_{t-1}$ to be uncorrelated but not independent — knowing $\\varepsilon_{t-1}$ tells us nothing about the mean of $\\varepsilon_t$, but may tell us something about its variance. This is precisely the situation in **ARCH models**: the residuals are uncorrelated, but their squared values are correlated. Such residuals are weak white noise but not IID noise.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
        "## Hierarchy of White Noise\n",
        "\n",
        "From strongest to weakest:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{IID noise} \\implies \\text{Strong white noise} \\implies \\text{Weak white noise}$$\n",
        "\n",
